  <entry>
    <id>https://www.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/133.0/releasenotes/</id>
    <title type="html">Thunderbird 133.0</title>
    <author>
      <name>Thunderbird</name>
      <uri>https://www.thunderbird.net</uri>
    </author>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/133.0/releasenotes/"/>
    <updated>2024-11-26T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <published>2024-11-26T00:00:00+00:00</published>

    <content type="html"><![CDATA[
      

  
  

  
    

    
      
        
        

        
          <h3>What’s New</h3>
        

        
        
          <ul>
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Support dark reader for the message pane</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        
          </ul>
        

        
          <h3>Changed</h3>
        

        
        
          <ul>
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Removed obsolete preference <code>extensions.overlayloader.loglevel</code></p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Increased the auto-compaction threshold to reduce frequency of compaction</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Display junk state and allow toggling it from top of message context menu</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Subscribe/Unsubscribe buttons were removed from the IMAP subscribe dialog</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        
          </ul>
        

        
          <h3>Fixed</h3>
        

        
        
          <ul>
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Fixed startup crash related to mailbox parsing</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Folder corruption could cause Thunderbird to freeze and become unusable</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>IMAP could crash when reading cached messages</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Enabling "Show Folder Size" on Maildir profile could render Thunderbird unusable</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Folder compaction was not abandoned on shutdown</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Recently deleted messages could become undeleted if message compaction failed</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Message corruption could be propagated when reading mbox</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Messages corrupted by folder compaction were only fixed by user intervention</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Reading a message from past the end of an mbox file did not cause an error</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>View -&gt; Folders had duplicate F access keys</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Total message count for favorite folders did not work consistently</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Collapsed NNTP thread incorrectly indicated there were unread messages</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Disabling "Grouped by sort" while group header selected could break message pane</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Switching from "All", "Unread", and "Threads with unread" did not work</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Navigating to next unread message did not wait for all messages to be loaded</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Folder compaction did not clean up on failure</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Add-ons adding columns to the message list could fail and cause display issue</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Could not open attached file in a MIME encrypted message</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Unable to send an unencrypted response to an OpenPGP encrypted message</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Remote content notifications were broken with encrypted messages</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Updating criteria of a saved search resulted in poor search performance</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Drag and drop of OS folders as attachments was not prevented</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Unable to generate QR codes when exporting to mobile in some cases</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Opening the Account Manager produced console error</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Account creation "Setup Documentation" link was broken</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>QR codes were not scannable by Android app when using most high-contrast themes</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Operating system reauthentication was missing when exporting QR codes for mobile</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>New mail notification was not hidden after reading the new message</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Windows "Notifications &amp; actions" did not display the Thunderbird icon</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>"Empty trash on exit" and "Expunge inbox on exit" did not always work</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Message could disappear after moving from IMAP folder followed by Undo and Redo</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Global database did not work immediately after update to Thunderbird 133</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Drop-downs may not work in some places</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Primary password prompt cancellation during mobile export was confusing</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Calendar display times could be incorrect</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Selected calendar day did not move forward at midnight</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Could not drag all-day events from one day to another in week view</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Calendar could show mixed languages in month display</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Calendar displayed incorrect first day of the week</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p>Visual and UX improvements</p>
          
        </li>
      
    
      
        
        

        

        
        

        
        

        <li>
          <p><a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/security/known-vulnerabilities/thunderbird/#thunderbird133">Security fixes</a></p>
          
        </li>
      
    
    </ul>
  
  

<p>As always, you’re encouraged to <a href="https://connect.mozilla.org/t5/ideas/idb-p/ideas/label-name/thunderbird">tell us what you think</a>, <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/questions/new/thunderbird">ask for help</a>, or <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/enter_bug.cgi?product=Thunderbird">file a bug in Bugzilla</a></p>
<style> li p { display: inline; } </style>
      ]]>
    </content>
  </entry>
  
